<p>You will need to choose a training provider to train your apprentice.</p><p><a href="https://www.apprenticeships.gov.uk/employer/find-apprenticeship-training" title="">Find apprenticeship training</a>Â will help you search for one by location, job role or keyword.</p><p>Your training provider can provide you with as much help and support as you need when you take on an apprentice.</p><p>Your training provider may also be able to help with:</p><ul><li><p>finding the right apprenticeship for you</p></li><li><p>preparing your apprentice for your organisation</p></li><li><p>making sure your apprentice is working in an appropriate environment</p></li><li><p>finding the right pace of learning for your apprentice</p></li><li><p>working with you to make sure your apprentice is learning the relevant skills</p></li></ul><p></p>
<h2>MISUNDERSTANDINGS AND MYTHS</h2>
<p>There are some misunderstandings and myths about what you can and can't do when working with a training provider. Here are a couple of examples:</p><ul><li><p>you can only work with one training provider at a time - not true, you can use a number of training providers</p></li><li><p>you can't get funding for over-24s - not true, you can get funding for apprenticeships depending on both your circumstances</p></li></ul><p></p>
